cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with unification, which is a fundamental concept in logic and type theory. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper deals with higher-order expressions and recursive let, which are common features in functional programming languages. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with the formal manipulation of expressions and the complexity of unification problems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of the unification algorithm. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the manipulation of expressions, which can be seen as a form of natural language processing.
